===Empress=== On January 1, 1683,{{efn|The 7th day of the 12th month of [[Tenna]] 2.}} Fusako was proclaimed {{Nihongo||准三后|jusangō}}, and on December 3{{efn|The 14th day of the 2nd month of Tenna 3.}} she was invested as ''[[:en:Chūgū|Chūgū]]''. She thereby became the emperor's legitimate wife—during the entire [[:en:Edo period|Edo period]], this only happened four times. Reigen abdicated the throne on May 2, 1687,{{efn|The 21st day of the 3rd month of [[Jōkyō]] 4.}} in favor of Crown Prince Asahito, who then became [[:en:Emperor Higashiyama|Emperor Higashiyama]]. Accompanying this, Fusako was bestowed the honorary name Shinjōsaimon-in. In early 1695,{{efn|The 7th month of [[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 8.}} the [[Tokugawa shogunate|shogunate]] presented her with 1,000 ''koku'' of land.
Takatsukasa Fusako died on May 19, 1712.{{efn|The 14th day of the 4th month of [[Shōtoku (era)|Shōtoku]] 4.}} Her grave is located at [[Tsuki no wa no misasagi]] in [[:en:Higashiyama-ku, Kyoto|Higashiyama-ku]], [[Kyoto]].
